'''Osanobua'''  is the name for God in the [[Edo language]]. It is often abbreviated as Osa, which is commonly integrated into modern Edo names, such as ''Esosa'', which means God's goodness or gift; ''Eghosa'', God's time; and ''Efosa'', God's blessings or wealth.

[[Edo State]] has several areas with their own local dialects; [[Esan people|Esan]], Ewohimi, Ewato, Ewosa, Etsako, Ora, [[Auchi]], [[Igueben]] and Iruekpen to mention but a few. The Esan people called God "Osenebra". It is often abbreviated as Ose. God is also described as "Ofuekenede" (merciful God), "Okakaludo" (stronger than stone), "Obonosuobo" (the great physician), etc.

